## Create a database as 'fidaa' :

```
 CREATE DATABASE fidaa;
 ```

## Select a database :

```
USE fidaa;
```
### Result :
Database changed

## Create a table named as 'user_info' :

```
CREATE TABLE user_info (id int PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT, email varchar(30) UNIQUE NOT NULL , dob date NOT NULL , gender ENUM('M','F','T','L','G'), profile_name varchar(10) UNIQUE NOT NULL DEFAULT 'fidaa_user');
```

## Describe a table named as 'user_info' :

```
 DESC user_info;
 ```
 ### Result :


| Field        | Type                      | Null | Key | Default    | Extra          |
|:------------:|:-------------------------:|:----:|:---:|:----------:|:--------------:|
| id           | int                       | NO   | PRI | NULL       | auto_increment |
| email        | varchar(30)               | NO   | UNI | NULL       |                |
| dob          | date                      | NO   |     | NULL       |                |
| gender       | enum('M','F','T','L','G') | YES  |     | NULL       |                |
| profile_name | varchar(10)               | NO   | UNI | fidaa_user |                |

## Create a table named as 'user_credentials'
```
CREATE TABLE user_credentials (user_id int NOT NULL,password varchar(20) UNIQUE NOT NULL, confirm_password varchar(20) UNIQUE NOT NULL, FOREIGN KEY(user_id) REFERENCES user_info(id));
```

## Create a table named as 'movies' :

```
CREATE TABLE movies(id int PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT, movie_name varchar(255) NOT NULL,poster blob, lang_id int,actor_id int,actress_id int,director_id int, FOREIGN KEY(lang_id) REFERENCES language(id),FOREIGN KEY(actor_id) REFERENCES actors(id),FOREIGN KEY(actress_id) REFERENCES actress(id),FOREIGN KEY(director_id) REFERENCES director(id));
```
## Describe the 'movies' table :

```
DESC movies;
```

### Result :

| Field       | Type         | Null | Key | Default | Extra          |
|:-----------:|:------------:|:----:|:---:|:-------:|:--------------:|
| id          | int          | NO   | PRI | NULL    | auto_increment |
| movie_name  | varchar(255) | YES  |     | NULL    |                |
| poster      | blob         | NO   |     | NULL    |                |
| lang_id     | int          | YES  | MUL | NULL    |                |
| actor_id    | int          | YES  | MUL | NULL    |                |
| actress_id  | int          | YES  | MUL | NULL    |                |
| director_id | int          | YES  | MUL | NULL    |                |

## Create a view named as 'user_details' by joining two tables :

```
CREATE VIEW user_details AS SELECT ui.email,ui.profile_name , uc.confirm_password FROM user_info ui, user_credentials uc WHERE ui.id = uc.user_id;
```
